# 04_resolver_list — post-migration registry inspection.
#
# Runs `list` and shows the registry's current contents. After s188 m1
# (toolbar funnel migration) this was fifteen entries — every tool
# button on the main toolbar registered under its widget_names.db
# abbrev. After s189 m1 (inspector migration) that grows by 49
# entries — every named Button / Entry / CheckButton / ToggleButton /
# DropDown construction site in PropertiesPanel.cpp now routes
# through curvz::widgets wrappers and registers in lock-step with
# its set_name abbrev.
#
# Sample of new inspector entries (selection — not exhaustive):
#
#   ins_blnd_rl   (inspector_blend_release_btn)
#   ins_blnd_rv   (inspector_blend_reverse_check)
#   ins_blnd_so   (inspector_blend_stroke_override_check)
#   ins_can_dpi   (inspector_canvas_dpi_dd)
#   ins_can_md    (inspector_canvas_mode_dd)
#   ins_can_un    (inspector_canvas_units_dd)
#   ins_grd_en    (inspector_grid_enable_check)
#   ins_grd_st    (inspector_grid_style_dd)
#   ins_mrg_en    (inspector_margins_enable_check)
#   ins_nod_cl    (inspector_node_path_closed_toggle)
#   ins_nod_tp    (inspector_node_type_dd)
#   ins_txt_b     (inspector_text_bold_check)
#   ins_txt_fam   (inspector_text_family_dd)
#   ins_fs_strk_cb / ..._cr / ..._cs  (cap toggles)
#   ins_fs_strk_jm / ..._jr / ..._jb  (join toggles)
#   …
#
# Carryover from s188 — toolbar entries still present:
#
#   tb_sel  tb_nod  tb_pen  tb_rec  tb_ova  tb_lin  tb_ref
#   tb_txt  tb_top  tb_pol  tb_spi  tb_eyd  tb_meas tb_zom  tb_cor
#
# Some inspector entries may render without a `(long_name)` decoration
# until `widget_names_sync` is re-run against the migrated source —
# same pattern as `tb_cor` in s188 (its set_name landed post-DB-rebuild
# and only re-syncing fills in the long_name column).
#
# This script is a sanity check, not an assertion-based test — read
# the output by eye.

list

